obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (29817)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755&sectionId=29817&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Dissolution of Muslim Marriages`
  line `Act, 1939.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1[^2***]^3`
  line .
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by Act 48 of 1959, s. 3 and Sch. I, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1960).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `3. In its application to Pondicherry, in section 1, after sub-section (2), the following shall be inserted--`
  line
  line `"Provided that nothing contained in this Act shall apply to the Renoncants of the Union territory of Pondicherry." Vide`
  line `(Act 26 of 1968).`
  line
  line `The Act has been extended to Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Sch. I.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (29818)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Grounds for decree for dissolution of marriage`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. The words "leprosy or" omitted by Act 6 of 2019, s. 3 (w.e.f 1-3-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755&sectionId=29818&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `A woman married under Muslim law shall be`
  line `entitle to obtain a decree for the dissolution of her marriage on any one or more of the following grounds,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the whereabouts of the husband have not been known for a period of four years;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the husband has neglected or has failed to provide for her maintenance for a period of two`
  line years;
  line
  line `(iii) that the husband has been sentenced to imprisonment for a period of seven years or upwards;`
  line
  line `(iv) that the husband has failed to perform, without reasonable cause, his marital obligations for a period of three years;`
  line
  line `(v) that the husband was impotent at the time of the marriage and continues to be so,`
  line
  line `(vi) that the husband has been insane for a period of two years or is suffering from ^3`
  line `*** a virulent venereal disease;`
  line
  line `(vii) that she, having been given in marriage by her father or other guardian before she attained the age of fifteen years, repudiated the marriage before attaining the age of eighteen years :`
  line
  line `Provided that the marriage has not been consummated ;`
  line
  line `(viii) that the husband treats her with cruelty, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) habitually assaults her or makes her life miserable by cruelty of conduct even if`
  line `such conduct does not amount to physical ill-treatment, or`
  line
  line `(b) associates with women of evil repute or leads an infamous life, or`
  line
  line `(c) attempts to force her to lead an immoral life, or`
  line
  line `(d) disposes of her property of prevents her exercising her legal rights over it, or`
  line
  line `(e) obstructs her in the observance of her religious profession or practice, or`
  line
  line `(f) if he has more wives than one, does not treat her equitably in accordance with the`
  line `injunctions of the Qoran;`
  line
  line `(ix) on any other ground which is recognised as valid for the dissolution of marriages`
  line `under muslim law :`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) no decree shall be passed on ground (iii) until the sentence has become final;`
  line
  line `(b) a decree passed on ground (i) shall not take effect for a period of six months from the date of such decree, and if the husband appears either in person or through an authorised agent within that period and satisfies the Court that he is prepared to perform his conjugal duties, the Court shall set aside the said decree; and`
  line
  line `(c) before passing a decree on ground (v) the Court shall, on application by the husband,`
  line `make an order requiring the husband to satisfy the Court within a period of one year from the date of such order that he has ceased to be impotent, and if the husband so satisfies the Court within such period, no decree shall be passed on the said ground.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (29821)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Notice to be served on heirs of the husband when the husband’s whereabouts are not known.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755&sectionId=29821&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In a suit to which clause (i) of section 2 applies--`
  line
  line `(a) the names and addresses of the persons who would have been the heirs of the husband under Muslim law if hehad died on the date of the filing of the plant shall be stated in the plaint,`
  line
  line `(b) notice of the suit shall be served on such persons, and`
  line
  line `(c) such persons shall have the right to be heard in the suit :`
  line
  line `Provided that paternal uncle and brother of the husband, if any, shall be cited as party even if he`
  line `or they are not heirs.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (29822)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Effect of conversion to another faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755&sectionId=29822&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The renunciation of Islam by a married Muslim`
  line `woman or her conversion to a faith other than Islam shall not by itself operate to dissolve her marriage :`
  line
  line `Provided that after such renunciation, or conversion, the woman shall be entitled to obtain a decree for the dissolution of her marriage on any of the grounds mentioned in section 2:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the provisions of this section shall not apply to a woman converted to Islam`
  line `from some other faith who re-embraces her former faith.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (29823)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Rights to dower not to be affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755&sectionId=29823&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall affect any right which a`
  line `married woman may have under Muslim law to her dower or any part thereof on the dissolution of her`
  line marriage.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (29824)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755&sectionId=29824&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00064_193908_1523352479755
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal of section 5 of Act 26 of`
  line `1937.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1942 (25 of 1942), s. 2 and the First Schedule .`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
